  "prompt": "What universities does Inteliquent recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Inteliquent, a company specializing in cloud communications and infrastructure services, typically recruits new graduates from universities with strong engineering, computer science, and business programs. While specific universities may vary, they often target institutions known for their STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering, and Mathematics) and business-related programs.\n\n### Universities Inteliquent May Recruit From:\n1. **Ivy League Schools** (e.g., Harvard, MIT, Stanford)\n2. **Top Engineering Schools** (e.g., Georgia Tech, University of Illinois Urbana-Champaign)\n3. **Business Schools** (e.g., University of Chicago Booth, Northwestern Kellogg)\n4. **State Universities** with strong STEM programs (e.g., University of Michigan, University of California system)\n\n### Majors Inteliquent Typically Looks For:\n1. **Computer Science/Computer Engineering**  \n2. **Electrical Engineering**  \n3. **Information Systems/Technology**  \n4. **Data Science/Analytics**  \n5. **Business Administration/Management**  \n6. **Telecommunications/Networking**  \n7. **Mathematics/Statistics**  \n\nInteliquent may also consider graduates with relevant internships, certifications, or project experience in telecommunications, cloud computing, or software development. For the most accurate and up-to-date information, check their official careers page or reach out to their HR department.",
